  }
  user_input {
    user_response: "I am building an IELTS Writing and Speaking Feedback App Platform. \n\nHere is how the application workflow operates:\n1. Input Layer: The app accepts user-submitted text files or transcripts representing practice IELTS essays and speaking responses.\n2. Analytics Layer: The system programmatically audits the submission against official IELTS public scoring rubrics across four core metrics (Task Achievement, Coherence, Vocabulary, and Grammar).\n3. Data Output Layer: The application structural engine converts this evaluation into a strict, machine-readable JSON data matrix containing individual band scores, a calculated overall band, and actionable correction bullet points.\n\nThe app\'s interface must prioritize clean data visualization over long, unstructured walls of text.\n"
    items {
      text: "I am building an IELTS Writing and Speaking Feedback App Platform. \n\nHere is how the application workflow operates:\n1. Input Layer: The app accepts user-submitted text files or transcripts representing practice IELTS essays and speaking responses.\n2. Analytics Layer: The system programmatically audits the submission against official IELTS public scoring rubrics across four core metrics (Task Achievement, Coherence, Vocabulary, and Grammar).\n3. Data Output Layer: The application structural engine converts this evaluation into a strict, machine-readable JSON data matrix containing individual band scores, a calculated overall band, and actionable correction bullet points.\n\nThe app\'s interface must prioritize clean data visualization over long, unstructured walls of text.\n"
    }
  }
}
