  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Verifying Final Outputs**\n\nI\'m pleased to report the compilation and initial run went flawlessly, no errors! My focus has now shifted to meticulously checking for any overlooked files that require verification. This ensures a comprehensive review before proceeding further. The user\'s input request is clear: I\'m set up to process text files or transcripts, specifically IELTS essays.\n\n\n**Refining UI Aesthetics**\n\nI\'ve successfully implemented all core IELTS scoring analytics and data output functionality; no code errors detected. My current focus is refining the user interface\'s aesthetic design. I\'m extracting styling elements, including colors, fonts, and spacing, to align with the desired \"Editorial Aesthetic\" theme. I\'m now applying these extracted styles across the data output layer.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully designed and built the **IELTS Writing and Speaking Feedback Engine**, fully integrated with our full-stack Express & Gemini architecture and meticulously styled after the **Editorial Aesthetic** design guidelines.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Aesthetic Design Pairing\n* **Editorial Palette**: Employs a sophisticated warm cream background (`#F9F8F6`) paired with high-contrast charcoal text (`#1A1A1A`) and elegant gold accents (`#C5A059`) to evoke an academic journal or formal certification atmosphere.\n* **Typographic Rhythm**: Paired graceful serif headings with clean monospace markers for metadata, scores, and log entries, creating an immediate hierarchy.\n* **Component Structures**: Organized into bento-style grids bordered with crisp dividers (`border-[#DEDCD7]`), mirroring standard paper scoring rubrics.\n\n### \342\232\231\357\270\217 Core Platform Functional Capabilities\n\n1. **Practice Input Modality Layer**\n   * **Writing Practice**: Supports rich text entry, dynamic word counters, and an interactive **drag-and-drop uploader** to parse `.txt` essays seamlessly.\n   * **Speaking Practice**: Fully integrated browser-native **microphone recording and real-time speech-to-text transcription** utilizing Web Speech API, allowing candidates to dictate responses and see transcripts load dynamically.\n   * **Test Presets**: Included ready-to-test mock prompts and candidate essays for immediate, friction-free testing of the evaluation capabilities.\n\n2. **Server-Side Analytics Layer**\n   * Proxies submissions securely to the **Gemini 3.5-flash** engine on our Express backend, preventing any client-side API key exposure.\n   * Evaluates input strictly against the four core IELTS public band rubrics: **Task Achievement / Response**, **Coherence & Cohesion**, **Lexical Resource**, and **Grammatical Range & Accuracy**.\n   * Employs programmatic rounding calculations to ensure that calculated overall band scores match the precise mathematical standards used by official IELTS examiners.\n\n3. **Data Output & Feedback Matrix**\n   * **Circular Band Visualizer**: Displays overall estimated scores elegantly within standard gold borders and detailed proficiency feedback cards.\n   * **Interactive Annotation Inspector**: High-priority grammatical, spelling, and lexical mistakes in the text are highlighted. Clicking a correction inside the interactive dark log box highlights the corresponding sentence in the candidate\'s text.\n   * **Detailed Remedial Action Plan**: Generates scannable, structured panels representing prominent strengths, primary impediments, and an actionable remedial plan.\n   * **Dossier Portfolio & Export**: All evaluations are securely cached in `localStorage` for progressive tracking. Candidates can copy the clean machine-readable JSON data matrix or trigger styled browser prints for physical feedback reporting."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 35644944
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
